sentences: Yae Fujimoto (藤本 八恵, Fujimoto Yae, born December 14, 1975), known as Yae, is a Japanese singer, mainly known outside Japan for having performed the theme songs for the GameCube role-playing video game Final Fantasy Crystal Chronicles.
She studied modern dance during high school, and decided to become a singer in 1999.
In June 2000, she debuted with the album "new Aeon".
2003 Kaze No Ne and Hoshizukiyo (Final Fantasy Crystal Chronicles, opening and ending theme songs)
2010 あいをよる おもいをつむぐ
2001 Blasa, The Legend of Condor Hero (神鵰俠侶 コンドルヒーロー, ending theme song)
2004 Shinsei (新生) and Michi (歌), Nitaboh, the Shamisen Master (NITABOH 仁太坊-津軽三味線始祖外聞, theme songs)
